    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix potential crash in is_UE_active function when called with invalid parameters\n\n### Summary\nThe `is_UE_active` function in `eNB_scheduler_primitives.c` could crash when called with invalid module_id or UE_id parameters. This fix adds proper parameter validation to prevent crashes and return a safe default value.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/eNB_scheduler_primitives.c`: Added validation checks for module_id and UE_id parameters in `is_UE_active` function\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/eNB_scheduler_primitives.c`: Added include for `common/openairinterface5g_limits.h` to access `NUMBER_OF_eNB_MAX` constant\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen the function `is_UE_active()` is called with an invalid module_id (>= NUMBER_OF_eNB_MAX) or invalid UE_id (< 0 or >= MAX_MOBILES_PER_ENB), it could previously cause a segmentation fault by accessing invalid memory addresses. With this fix, the function now safely returns `false` for invalid parameters.\n\nThe issue was particularly noticeable during debugging sessions where the function was called from assertion messages in error conditions, causing secondary crashes that obscured the original problem.\n\n"
}